Thanks for the support guys, that's really nice.<br>
<br>
I'm only a level 51 Mage, and a level 61 Necro. I play both and love both. I have to focus on one so I play the Necro mostly. I also have a level 58 Cleric and take an avid role on some Cleric boards as well. I love all three classes. (And I'm starting to really like Rogues heh.)<br>
<br>
Anyway, when I was a level 30 Mage I felt bad to see Wizards not nuking as powerfuly as I was.<br>
<br>
As for the high end game? I have a lot of level 61+ Mage guildies and a few 61+ Wizard guildies. I'm just speaking from my observations of them and their conversations and from my personal experience as a low level Mage.<br>
<br>
I'd NEVER cry nerf or ask Verant to change anything like that. I just question their judgement when it comes to things like this.<br>
<br>
I think it's great that the Mage bolt was on a vendor, I just think the Wizard nook shoulda been vendor sold and made at level 61 as well. That's just my opinion.<br>
<br>
Two other side notes since the topic came up:<br>
<br>
1: I'm an Evoc Mage <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  And since the Mod Rod change I will stay Evoc. (I had planned on changing at level 57, but not now.)<br>
<br>
2: I would (And have in the past.) speak my heart about Necromancer issues as well, even if it didn't benefit my class as a whole, please don't think I'm suffering from lack of insight.<br>
<br>
I think it was wrong for Verant to put three of the BEST 61+ Necro spells AT level 61.<br>
<br>
- We get our best pet at 61 (60 Warrior pet.. sometimes he tanks so well and does so much damage I think he's broken...)<br>
<br>
- Best (And only) Lifetap upgrade at 61 (Crittable/Focusable 850 point 3 second cast time, 1k+ with Foci.)<br>
<br>
- Our biggest nuke at level 61 (With Focus IV items it's a crittable 1512 nuke, which in itself is kinda wierd since we're not nookers!)<br>
<br>
Kinda makes it tough for me to choose to progress beyond that.<br>
